Sentencas: Anode-supported solid state fuel cells (SOFCs) based on composite anode NiO-La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-delta-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-delta were fabricated by dry-pressing process.
Titulo: NiO-La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ-Ce0.8SM0.2O2-δ composite anode for natural gas in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The composite cathode and electrolyte were consisted of La0.8Sr0.2Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta(LSCF)-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-delta(GDC) and Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-delta(GDC), respectively.
Titulo: NiO-La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ-Ce0.8SM0.2O2-δ composite anode for natural gas in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The performance of single cell used humidified natural gas(3% H2O) as fuel and oxygen was tested as oxidant was tested from 400 T to 700 degrees C.
Titulo: NiO-La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ-Ce0.8SM0.2O2-δ composite anode for natural gas in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The chemical stability, microstructures and carbon deposition have been investivaged using XRD, SEM, EDX.
Titulo: NiO-La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ-Ce0.8SM0.2O2-δ composite anode for natural gas in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The results show that composite anode and composite cathode are with better pore microstructure, and the composite anode has good chemical compatibility.
Titulo: NiO-La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ-Ce0.8SM0.2O2-δ composite anode for natural gas in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: EDX measurements showed only a small carbon peaks.
Titulo: NiO-La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ-Ce0.8SM0.2O2-δ composite anode for natural gas in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: We have also tested the stability of the single cell at 600 degrees C for 13 h. The results show that the composite anode exhibits better stability and no degradation is observed in 13 h testing periods.
Titulo: NiO-La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ-Ce0.8SM0.2O2-δ composite anode for natural gas in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The result of performance tests indicate that the maximum output current density and power density are 215.49 mA center dot cm(-2) and 44.85 mW center dot cm(-2) at 600 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: NiO-La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ-Ce0.8SM0.2O2-δ composite anode for natural gas in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell
